## ğŸ”§ **Hardware Compatibility Matrix**

<div align="center">

### ğŸ¯ **Tested & Verified ESP8266 Boards**

</div>

| Board | Status | Flash Size | GPIO Pins | Special Features |
|-------|--------|------------|-----------|------------------|
| **NodeMCU v1.0** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 11 usable | Built-in USB, LED on pin 2 |
| **NodeMCU v0.9** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 11 usable | Older version, fully compatible |
| **Wemos D1 Mini** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 11 usable | Compact size, perfect for projects |
| **Wemos D1 R2** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 11 usable | Arduino Uno form factor |
| **ESP8266-01** | âš ï¸ Limited Support | 1MB | 2 usable | Minimal pins, requires adapter |
| **ESP8266-12E** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 16 usable | Raw module, requires breakout |
| **ESP8266-12F** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 16 usable | Improved antenna design |
| **Adafruit Feather HUZZAH** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 9 usable | Battery connector, compact |
| **SparkFun ESP8266 Thing** | âœ… Fully Supported | 4MB | 11 usable | LiPo charging circuit |
| **Generic ESP8266** | âœ… Usually Supported | Varies | Varies | Most ESP8266 boards work |

### ğŸ”Œ **Pin Configuration Reference**

#### **NodeMCU Pin Mapping**
```
NodeMCU Pin | ESP8266 GPIO | Function | ESP-Linker Support
------------|--------------|----------|-------------------
D0          | GPIO16       | Digital  | âœ… Digital I/O only
D1          | GPIO5        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
D2          | GPIO4        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
D3          | GPIO0        | Digital  | âœ… Digital I/O (Boot pin)
D4          | GPIO2        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + LED
D5          | GPIO14       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
D6          | GPIO12       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
D7          | GPIO13       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
D8          | GPIO15       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo
A0          | ADC0         | Analog   | âœ… 10-bit ADC input
```

#### **Wemos D1 Mini Pin Mapping**
```
D1 Mini Pin | ESP8266 GPIO | Function | ESP-Linker Support
------------|--------------|----------|-------------------
D0          | GPIO16       | Digital  | âœ… Digital I/O only
D1          | GPIO5        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + I2C SCL
D2          | GPIO4        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + I2C SDA
D3          | GPIO0        | Digital  | âœ… Digital I/O (Flash button)
D4          | GPIO2        | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Built-in LED
D5          | GPIO14       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + SPI CLK
D6          | GPIO12       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + SPI MISO
D7          | GPIO13       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + SPI MOSI
D8          | GPIO15       | Digital  | âœ… Digital + PWM + Servo + SPI CS
A0          | ADC0         | Analog   | âœ… 10-bit ADC (0-1024)
```

### âš¡ **Power Requirements**
- **Operating Voltage**: 3.3V (regulated on most boards)
- **Input Voltage**: 5V via USB or 7-12V via Vin pin
- **Current Consumption**:
  - Active: ~80mA
  - Deep Sleep: ~20ÂµA
  - WiFi Transmit: ~170mA peak

### ğŸ”§ **Connection Requirements**
- **USB Cable**: Micro-USB (NodeMCU) or USB-C (newer boards)
- **WiFi Network**: 2.4GHz (ESP8266 doesn't support 5GHz)
- **Computer**: Windows/Linux/macOS with Python 3.7+

## ğŸ“š API Reference

### ESPBoard Class
```python
class ESPBoard:
    def __init__(self, ip_or_url: str, timeout: float = 10.0)
    def write(self, pin: int, value: int) -> bool
    def read(self, pin: int) -> int
    def analog_read(self) -> int
    def pwm(self, pin: int, value: int) -> bool
    def servo(self, pin: int, angle: int) -> bool
    def get_device_info(self) -> dict
    def ping(self) -> bool
    def close(self) -> None
```

### Utility Functions
```python
def connect_auto(timeout: float = 10.0) -> ESPBoard
def discover_devices(timeout: float = 30.0) -> List[dict]
def flash_esp8266(port: str = None, baud: int = 115200) -> bool
def detect_esp8266() -> List[str]
```

## ğŸ¯ **Real-World Use Cases & Project Examples**

<div align="center">

### ğŸŒŸ **Transform Ideas into Reality**

</div>

<details>
<summary><h3>ğŸ  <strong>Smart Home Automation</strong></h3></summary>

Create intelligent home automation systems with ESP-Linker:

#### ğŸ’¡ **Smart Lighting Control**
```python
from esp_linker import connect_auto
import time

board = connect_auto()

# Smart dimming based on time of day
def auto_dimming():
    current_hour = time.localtime().tm_hour
    if 6 <= current_hour <= 8:      # Morning
        board.pwm(2, 300)           # 30% brightness
    elif 18 <= current_hour <= 22:  # Evening
        board.pwm(2, 700)           # 70% brightness
    else:                           # Night
        board.pwm(2, 100)           # 10% brightness

auto_dimming()
```

#### ğŸŒ¡ï¸ **Climate Control System**
```python
# Temperature-based fan control
temp_sensor = board.analog_read()  # Temperature sensor on A0
temp_celsius = (temp_sensor * 3.3 / 1024 - 0.5) * 100

if temp_celsius > 25:
    board.pwm(5, 1023)  # Full speed fan
elif temp_celsius > 22:
    board.pwm(5, 512)   # Half speed fan
else:
    board.pwm(5, 0)     # Fan off
```

#### ğŸšª **Smart Door Lock**
```python
# RFID-controlled door lock
def check_access_card():
    card_detected = board.read(4)  # RFID reader signal
    if card_detected:
        board.servo(14, 90)        # Unlock (servo to 90Â°)
        time.sleep(5)
        board.servo(14, 0)         # Lock (servo to 0Â°)
```

</details>

